SDEV-M01 Module Overview - Algorithms
In this section, you will be introduced to algorithms, logic development, and flowcharting as tools to understanding computer logic.  In this module you will learn how to successfully focus on Problem Solving and Algorithms. Problem solving and algorithm development is the basis for software development. Problem solving is where a plan is developed to help to solve the problem. An algorithm is the instructions taken to solve the problem and the Program Development Cycle.  You will also learn about input/processing/output and integer and floating point data.  

SDEV Section & Module Objectives
By the end of this module, you will be able to:

Apply critical thinking and problem solving methodologies.
Break problems down to identify the problem, determine the key pieces of data needed to solve the problem, generate possible solutions, select the best option and execute
Define the Software Development Life Cycle as it pertains to software development and problem solving.
Apply the problem-solving strategy for computer programming problems
Describe the basic components of a computer program: input, processing and output
Identify the uses of various programming and scripting languages in computer systems.
Define and describe what programs are, and in a very general way, how they are written
Write generic program statements that perform input, processing and output
Name and use constants and variables in a program
Define and use string and data character data types